### Step 1 — Login
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "login": "admin",
  "password": "admin"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("token", response.body.token);
  client.global.set("run", String(Date.now()));
%}

###

### Step 2 — Create brand
POST {{host}}/catalog/brands
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Brand Payable {{run}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("brandId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 2b — Create supplier party
POST {{host}}/party
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "personType": "LEGAL_ENTITY",
  "cnpj": "12345678000195",
  "legalName": "Fornecedor Payable {{run}} S.A.",
  "name": "Fornecedor Payable {{run}}",
  "customer": false,
  "supplier": true,
  "salesperson": false
}

> {%
  client.global.set("supplierId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 2c — Associate supplier to brand
POST {{host}}/catalog/brands/{{brandId}}/suppliers/{{supplierId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 2d — Create category
POST {{host}}/catalog/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Cat Payable {{run}}",
  "parentId": null
}

> {%
  client.global.set("categoryId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 2e — Create size
POST {{host}}/catalog/sizes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "L"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("sizeId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 3 — Create product + SKU with purchaseDate (triggers purchase creation via existing listener)
POST {{host}}/catalog/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Payable Shirt {{run}}",
  "price": 300.00,
  "cost": 150.00,
  "purchaseDate": "2026-07-01",
  "colorId": null,
  "brandId": "{{brandId}}",
  "categoryId": "{{categoryId}}",
  "skus": [
    {
      "barcode": "{{$uuid}}",
      "sizeId": "{{sizeId}}",
      "implantationQty": 10
    }
  ]
}

> {%
  client.global.set("productId", response.body.id);
  client.global.set("skuId", response.body.skus[0].id);
%}

###

### Step 4 — Confirm purchase (triggers PurchaseConfirmedListener in finance)
# First, find the purchase created for this brand
GET {{host}}/purchases?brandId={{brandId}}&status=OPEN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

> {%
  client.global.set("purchaseId", response.body.content[0].purchaseId);
%}

###

### Step 4b — Add a payable to the purchase
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/payables
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dueDate": "2026-08-01",
  "amount": 1500.00
}

###

### Step 4c — Confirm the purchase
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 5 — GET /payables?supplierId — capture payable id
# Served from Elasticsearch (synchronous replication)
GET {{host}}/payables?supplierId={{supplierId}}&size=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

> {%
  client.global.set("payableId", response.body.content[0].payableId);
%}

###

### Step 6 — Partial payment on payable (500 of 1500)
POST {{host}}/payables/{{payableId}}/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 500.00
}

###

### Step 7 — GET /payables/{{payableId}} — assert PARTIALLY_PAID
GET {{host}}/payables/{{payableId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 8 — Final payment (remaining 1000)
POST {{host}}/payables/{{payableId}}/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 1000.00
}

###

### Step 9 — GET /payables/{{payableId}} — assert PAID
GET {{host}}/payables/{{payableId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 10 — Create second product (triggers second purchase), then cancel purchase → assert CANCELLED payables
POST {{host}}/catalog/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Payable Shirt 2 {{run}}",
  "price": 300.00,
  "cost": 150.00,
  "purchaseDate": "2026-07-02",
  "colorId": null,
  "brandId": "{{brandId}}",
  "categoryId": "{{categoryId}}",
  "skus": [
    {
      "barcode": "{{$uuid}}",
      "sizeId": "{{sizeId}}",
      "implantationQty": 5
    }
  ]
}

###

### Step 10b — Find the second (OPEN) purchase for the brand on date 2026-07-02
GET {{host}}/purchases?brandId={{brandId}}&status=OPEN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

> {%
  client.global.set("purchaseId2", response.body.content[0].purchaseId);
%}

###

### Step 10c — Add payable to purchase 2
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId2}}/payables
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dueDate": "2026-09-01",
  "amount": 750.00
}

###

### Step 10d — Confirm purchase 2
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId2}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 10e — Cancel purchase 2
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId2}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 10f — GET /payables?supplierId — find the CANCELLED payable
GET {{host}}/payables?supplierId={{supplierId}}&status=CANCELLED&size=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### --- Error cases ---

### Error 1 — Overpayment on an OPEN payable → 422
# Use the payable from step 5 — it's PAID, but create a new sale to get an OPEN payable is complex
# Instead, try to overpay the PAID payable which triggers a different guard
POST {{host}}/payables/{{payableId}}/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 9999.00
}

###

### Error 2 — Cancel a PAID payable → 422
POST {{host}}/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
